obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34831)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 1st June, 1910, see Gazette of India, 1910, Pt. I, p. 411.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34831&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Museum Act,`
  line 1910.
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34832)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Constitution and incorporation of the Trustees of the Indian Museum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `2. Subs. by Act 45 of 1960, s. 2, for sub-section (1).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34832&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The`
  line `Trustees of the Indian Museum (hereinafter referred to as the Trustees) shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) the Governor of West Bengal, ex officio Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) the Secretary to the. Government of India in the Ministry concerned with matters relating to`
  line `the Indian Museum, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) the Mayor of the Corporation of Calcutta, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Vice-Chancellor of the University of Calcutta, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Accountant-General, West Bengal, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) four persons to be nominated by the Central Government, one of whom shall be a`
  line `representative of commerce and industry chosen in consultation with the Government of`
  line `West Bengal;`
  line
  line `(g) one person to be nominated by the Government of West Bengal;`
  line
  line `(h) one person to be nominated by the Council of the Asiatic Society, Calcutta:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any of the Trustees referred to in clauses (b), (c) (d) and (e) is unable to attend any`
  line `meeting of the Trustees, he may, with the previous approval of the Chairman, authorise a person in`
  line `writing to do so.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Trustees shall be a body corporate, by the name of "The Trustees of the Indian Museum",`
  line `with perpetual succession and a common seal, and in that name shall sue and be sued, and shall have`
  line `power to acquire and hold property, to enter into contracts, and to do all acts necessary for and consistent`
  line `with the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The nominated Trustees shall, save as herein otherwise provided, hold office for a period of three`
  line `years:`
  line
  line `Provided that the authority nominating a Trustee may extend his term of office for one or more like`
  line periods.
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34833)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Minimum number of Trustees and quorum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34833&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The powers of the said body corporate may`
  line `only be exercised so long and so often as there are ^1[six] members thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The quorum necessary for the transaction of business at a meeting of the Trustees shall not be less`
  line `than ^2[four].`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "nine".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "six".`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34834)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to appoint new Trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 45 of 1960, s. 4, ibid., for "any office specified in section 2, clause (a)".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34834&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `If a nominated Trustee--`
  line
  line `(a) dies, or`
  line
  line `(b) is absent from the meetings of the Trustees for more than twelve consecutive months, or`
  line
  line `(c) desires to be discharged, or`
  line
  line `(d) refuses or becomes incapable to act, or`
  line
  line `(e) is appointed to perform the duties of ^1[any of the offices specified in clauses (a) to (e) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2],`
  line
  line `the authority which nominated the Trustee may nominate a new Trustee in his place.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34835)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34835&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `[Vacation of office by existing Trustees.] omitted by the Indian Museum`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1960 (45 of 1960), s. 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34836)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Property vested in or placed under the control of the Trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Rep. by this Act, s. 17.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34836&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) All the property,`
  line `whether movable or immovable, which at the commencement of this Act is held by the Trustees of the`
  line `Indian Museum constituted by the ^1Indian Museum Act, 1876 (22 of 1876) on trust for the purposes of the`
  line `said Museum shall, together with any such property which may hereinafter be given, bequeathed,`
  line `transferred or acquired for the said purposes, vest in the Trustees of the Indian Museum constituted by`
  line `this Act on trust for the purposes of the said Museum:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Trustees may expend the capital of any portion of such property which may consist`
  line `of money on the maintenance, improvement and enlargement of the collections deposited in, presented to`
  line `or purchased for, the said Museum or otherwise for the purposes of the same as they may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Trustees shall have the exclusive possession, occupation and control, for the purposes of such`
  line `trust, of the land specified in the schedule, including any buildings which may have been, or may`
  line `hereafter be, erected thereon, other than those portions thereof which have been set apart by the Trustees`
  line `for the records and offices of the Geological Survey of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (34837)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to Trustees to exchange, sell and destroy articles in collections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "the Provinces".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34837&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the`
  line `provisions of any bye-laws made in this behalf, the Trustees may, from time to time,--`
  line
  line `(a) deliver, by way of loan, to any person the whole or any portion of, or any article contained in,`
  line `any collection vested in them under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) exchange or sell duplicates of articles contained in any such collection and take or purchase,`
  line `in the place of such duplicates, such articles as may in their opinion be worthy of preservation in the`
  line Museum;
  line
  line `(c) present duplicates of articles contained in any such collection to other Museums in ^1[India];`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) remove and destroy any article contained in any such collection.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34838)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to Trustees to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34838&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) the Trustees may from time to time, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the Central Government,`
  line `^1[make by notification in the Official Gazette, bye-laws]`
  line `consistent with this Act ^2[and the rules made thereunder] for any purpose necessary for the execution of`
  line `their trust.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such ^3[bye-laws] may provide`
  line for--
  line
  line `(a) the summoning, holding and adjournment of general and special meetings of the Trustees;`
  line
  line `(b) the securing of the attendance of Trustees at such meetings;`
  line
  line `(c) the provision and keeping of minute-books and account-books;`
  line
  line `(d) the compiling of catalogues;`
  line
  line `(e) the lending of articles contained in the collections vested in the Trustees;`
  line
  line `(f) the exchange and sale, and the presentation to other Museums in ^4[India], of duplicates of articles`
  line `contained in such collections;`
  line
  line `(g) the removal and destruction of articles contained in such collections; and`
  line
  line `(h) the general management of the Museum.`
  line
  line `^5[(3) The Central Government shall cause every bye-law made under this section to be laid as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the bye-law or both Houses agree that the bye-law should not be made, the bye-law shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that`
  line bye-law.]
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule, for"make bye-laws" (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 45 of 1960, s. 6.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 45 of 1960, s. 6 for "rules".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for"the Provinces".`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (34839)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power of Trustees to appoint officers and servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `13. Subs. by Act 45 of 1960, s. 7, for section 9.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34839&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Power of Trustees to appoint officers and servants.--(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2),`
  line `the Trustees may appoint such officers and servants as they may consider necessary or proper for the care or`
  line `management of the trust-property, and determine their functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The recruitment and the conditions of service of such officers and servants shall be regulated by rules`
  line `made under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (34850)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for section 10.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34850&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10. Budget.--The Trustees shall, by such date in each financial year as may be specified by the Central`
  line `Government, submit to that Government for approval, in the form specified by that Government in consultation`
  line `with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, the budget of the next financial year, showing the estimated`
  line `receipts and expenditure during the next financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (42832)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Annual report and accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=42832&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `10A. Annual report and accounts.--(1) The Trustees shall, as soon as possible after the commencement of`
  line `each financial year, submit--`
  line
  line `(a) to the Central Government within such time or date as may be specified by the Central Government, a`
  line `report giving a true and full account of their activities during the previous financial year and an account of the`
  line `activities likely to be undertaking during the current financial year;`
  line
  line `(b) to such auditor as the Central Government may appoint in this behalf, accounts of all moneys`
  line `expended by the Trustees during the previous financial year, supported by the necessary vouchers.`
  line
  line `(2) The Trustees shall cause such report and accounts to be published annually for general information.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (34841)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Collections of Asiatic Society to be kept distinguished in the museum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34841&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Trustees shall`
  line `cause every article in the collections in the said Indian Museum formerly belonging to the Asiatic Society of`
  line `Bengal ^1[(now known as the Asiatic Society, Calcutta)] and all additions that may hereafter be made thereto`
  line `otherwise than by purchase under section 6, to be marked and numbered and (subject to the provisions contained`
  line `in sections 7 and 16) to be kept and preserved in the said Museum with such marks and numbers.`
  line
  line `(2) An inventory of such additions shall be made by the said Society, one copy whereof shall be signed by the`
  line `Trustees and delivered to the said society, and another copy shall be signed by the Council of the said Society and`
  line `delivered to the Trustees, and shall be kept by them along with the inventory delivered to the predecessors in`
  line `office of the Trustees when the said collections were deposited in the said Museum.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (34851)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Articles received in exchange or purchased and moneys realised from sale to be held on trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34851&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `All objects taken in exchange and articles purchased under section 7 and all moneys realised from sales`
  line `made in accordance with the terms of the same section shall be held on trust and subject to powers and`
  line `declarations corresponding as nearly as may be with the trusts, powers and declarations by this Act limited and`
  line declared.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (34843)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 14
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions to Trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 45 of 1960, s. 10.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34843&sectionno=12A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Power of Central Government to issue directions to Trustees.--(1) In the discharge of their`
  line `functions under this Act, the Trustees shall be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the`
  line `Central Government may give to them from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Trustees shall be given an opportunity to express their views before any direction is given`
  line `under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (34844)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Officers under Act to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Certain words omitted by s. 11, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34844&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `All officers and servants appointed under this Act shall`
  line `be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860); ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (34845)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to Trustees to keep collections not belonging to them.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34845&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `hereinbefore contained, the Trustees may, if they think fit, with the previous sanction of the Central Government`
  line `and subject in each case to such conditions as it may approve and to such rules as it may prescribe, assume the`
  line `custody and administration of collections which are not the property of the Trustees for the purposes of their trust`
  line `under this Act, and keep and preserve such collections either in the Indian Museum or elsewhere:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the trust constituted by this Act is at any time determined, any such collections shall not by`
  line `reason of their then being in the Indian Museum become the property of Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (34846)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to Trustees to part with certain property in their possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for the original section.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34846&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Power to Trustees to part with certain property in their possession.--Subject to such`
  line `conditions as the Central Government may approve, the Trustees may deliver possession of the whole or`
  line `any part of the property described in the schedule to such person as that Government may appoint.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (34847)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34847&sectionno=15A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Power to make rules.--(1) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Trustees, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all`
  line `or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the recruitment and the conditions of service of the officers and servants of the Museum;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner in which the accounts of the Museum may be maintained and the manner in`
  line `which such accounts may be audited;`
  line
  line `(c) the circumstances in which and the conditions subject to which the Trustees may assume the`
  line `custody and administration of any collections referred to in section 14 and keep and preserve such`
  line collections;
  line
  line `(d) the conditions subject to which the Trustees may deliver possession of any property in their possession`
  line `to any other person.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each House of`
  line `Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or ^2[in two`
  line `or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule, or both Houses agree`
  line `that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect,`
  line `as the case may be; so however that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity`
  line `of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 45 of 1960, s. 12.`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (34848)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 19
  title `Property in collections on determination of trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850&sectionId=34848&sectionno=16&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00014_191010_1523341315850
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If the trust constituted by this Act is at any time`
  line determined,--
  line
  line `(a) the collections and additions mentioned in section 11 shall become the property of the said Asiatic`
  line `Society or their assigns, and`
  line
  line `(b) all the other collections then in the said Indian Museum shall, save as otherwise provided by section`
  line `14, become the property of Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
